inn1.comm: big shout for lbw. He was on the back foot and it looked close. May have missed the off stump
off the mark with a clip through square-leg
good leave - but only just, the ball went just over off stump
half-volley driven through cover point, good shot
just a little shorter and Watts doesn't offer a shot
well bowled, Watts got caught on the crease there and was hit on the pad, it was too high though
full ball driven straight to mid off, awful fielding allows a single
big drive outside off, it wasn't quite full enough for that shot and he gets a thin edge. Good diving catch by Ramdin to his right.
dropped; flicked off the front foot to square leg. Smith leaps but can only get one hand to it, a tough chance.
another boundary, this time through cover. It was a half volley but well put away
fantastic shot, picked up over midwicket. It was a full delivery on middle stump
too straight from Smith, turned out to deep square-leg
another quick single to mid-off, who appears a little deep on the edge of the fielding circle
that was a quick delivery, full and on off-stump, Hussain plays to gully where Smith fields well
straight ball turned to square-leg. Hussain wants a run but Poonia sends him back
full ball on leg stump, swung down to fine-leg. They come back for a sharply run single
quick single to mid-on. The fielder hits with an under-arm throw but he's safe
